
[1]bulwark

   BUL'WARK, n.

   1. In fortification, a bastion, or a rampart; a mound of earth round a
   place, capable of resisting cannon shot, and formed with bastions,
   curtains, &c.

   2. A fortification; also, any means of defense; as, a navy is the
   bulwark of a nation.

   3. That which secures against an enemy or external annoyance; a screen
   or shelter; means of protection and safety.

   Salvation will God appoint for walls and bulwarks. Is.26.

   BUL'WARK, v.t. To fortify with a rampart; to secure by a fortification;
                                 to protect.
